The paper deals with motion planning and optimization for legged robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of wrench-based feasibility analysis and optimization techniques suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of computer vision (cs.CV) for terrain analysis and perception, and the optimization techniques used could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
